# Individual: <https://w3id.org/pmd/distel/DISTEL_0000012> (stress-controlled)

AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label <https://w3id.org/pmd/distel/DISTEL_0000012> "stress-controlled"@en)
AnnotationAssertion(<http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#altLabel> <https://w3id.org/pmd/distel/DISTEL_0000012> "force-controlled"@en)
AnnotationAssertion(<http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#altLabel> <https://w3id.org/pmd/distel/DISTEL_0000012> "load-controlled"@en)
AnnotationAssertion(<http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> <https://w3id.org/pmd/distel/DISTEL_0000012> "A fatigue test is considered stress-controlled if a laod/force ratio of a load exerted on a specimen is kept constant."@en)

# Individual: <https://w3id.org/pmd/distel/DISTEL_0000015> (compression-compression loading)

AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label <https://w3id.org/pmd/distel/DISTEL_0000015> "compression-compression loading"@en)
AnnotationAssertion(<http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> <https://w3id.org/pmd/distel/DISTEL_0000015> "Compression-compression loading is a type of axial loading. A specimen is compresed and then returned to its original length."@en)

# Individual: <https://w3id.org/pmd/distel/DISTEL_0000016> (room temperature)

AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:comment <https://w3id.org/pmd/distel/DISTEL_0000016> "TODO there is abn abbreviation AP in PMDco")
AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label <https://w3id.org/pmd/distel/DISTEL_0000016> "room temperature"@en)
AnnotationAssertion(<http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#altLabel> <https://w3id.org/pmd/distel/DISTEL_0000016> "RT"@en)
AnnotationAssertion(<http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> <https://w3id.org/pmd/distel/DISTEL_0000016> "Room temperature is a value specification, which vaguely describes the temperature usually during some process. It leaves a room for interpretation which exact temperature is meant."@en)
ClassAssertion(<http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/OBI_0001933> <https://w3id.org/pmd/distel/DISTEL_0000016>)

